Package: ppso
Type: Package
Title: Particle Swarm Optimization, optionally using parallel computing based on Rmpi
Version: 0.9-5
Date: 2009-08-14
Author: Till Francke
Maintainer: Till Francke <francke@uni-potsdam.de>
Description: ppso, (Parallel) Particle Swarm Optimization, provides optimization capabilities for a given objective function f. It adjusts the parameter vector p to produce a minimum value of f. \nThis algorithm especially excells for multidimensional (multi-parameter) functions with many local extrema. The parallelized version builds on Rmpi and is intended for highly computationally intensive objective functions (>20 s evaluation time).  -- experimental version, use with care. Comments welcome --
Depends: R (>= 2.8.0)
Suggests: Rmpi (>= 0.5-7), rgl, lhs
License:  WTFPL
